President Barack Obama will be addressing the Cincinnati AFL-CIO Labor Day Picnic in Cincinnati, OH. The picnic is hosted by the Cincinnati AFL-CIO Labor Council and is open to the public. Ed Montgomery, Executive Director of the White House Council on Automotive Communities and Workers, will also be in attendance. The program will include various speakers and participants, including Secretary Hilda Solis, Charles "Charlie" Dilbert, and several Ohio politicians and union leaders. The event is expected to draw a large crowd, with approximately 10,000 tickets distributed to affiliates of the Cincinnati AFL-CIO Labor Council.